全球首例新冠肺炎病人肺移植手术成功。
The world's first lung transplant in a patient with new crown pneumonia was successful.
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
匡小颖/北京头条客户端3月1日，北京青年报记者从著名肺移植专家陈静瑜处了解到，2月29日，陈静瑜团队在无锡成功进行全球首例新冠肺炎双肺移植手术。
Kuang Xiaoying / Beijing Headline Client March 1, Beijing Youth Daily reporters from the renowned lung transplant experts Chen Jingyu learned that on February 29, Chen Jing Yu's team in Wuxi successfully carried out the world's first two-lung transplant of new crown pneumonia.
患者为59岁男性，确诊新冠肺炎后，经过插管+ECMO和药物治疗后，连续核酸检测呈阴性，但双肺功能已严重受损且不可逆。
The patient, a 59-year-old man, was tested negative for continuous nucleic acid after being diagnosed with Newcomial Pneumonia with intubation + ECMO and medication, but his lung function was severely impaired and irreversible.
患者术后状态平稳。
The patient was in stable condition after operation.
业内专家认为，这例新冠肺炎危重症病例肺移植救治手段对降低死亡率有较大意义。
Industry experts believe that this new crown pneumonia critical case of lung transplantation treatment is of great significance to reduce mortality.
3月1日凌晨，无锡全国人大代表、中日友好医院肺移植科主任、南医大无锡市人民医院副院长陈静瑜发文称，无锡完成首例新冠肺炎肺移植。
In the early morning of March 1, Chen Jingyu, deputy NPC deputy and director of lung transplantation at the China-Japan Friendship Hospital and vice-president of Wuxi Municipal People's Hospital, said Wuxi had completed its first lung transplant.
3月1日上午，北青报记者从陈静瑜处了解到，2月29日在江苏省卫健委、省防控医疗专家全力支持下，陈静瑜团队历经5个小时鏖战在无锡成功进行全球首例新冠肺炎病例双肺移植手术。
On the morning of March 1, the Beijing Youth Daily learned from Chen Jingyu that on February 29, with the full support of the Jiangsu Provincial Health Care Commission and provincial medical experts, Chen Jingyu's team successfully performed the world's first two-lung transplant in Wuxi after a five-hour struggle.
该新冠肺炎病例在江苏省，男，59岁，1月23日发病，1月26日确诊COVID-19，2月7日气管插管，2月22日ECMO，2月24日转至无锡市传染病医院，病人经气管插管+ECMO和药物治疗后，连续核酸检测呈阴性，但双肺功能已严重受损且不可逆。
The case was diagnosed on January 23, COVID-19 was diagnosed on January 26, ECMO on February 22, and transferred to Wuxi Infectious Disease Hospital on February 24. Patients tested negative for continuous nucleic acid after trachea intubation + ECMO and drug therapy, but their lung function was severely impaired and irreversible.
2月29日，在江苏省卫健委支持下，无锡市卫生系统打破常规、整合一切医疗资源，由陈静瑜教授团队对该病例进行了双肺移植手术。
On February 29, with the support of the Jiangsu Provincial Health Committee, the Wuxi City Health System broke routine and consolidated all medical resources.
肺源系外地脑死亡患者爱心捐献，在外省获取经高铁转运7小时至无锡。
Lung source patients with brain death from overseas donation, access to the province via high-speed rail transit 7 hours to Wuxi.
截至目前，该病人术后已经清醒，移植双肺功能氧合良好，生命体征平稳。
Up to now, the patient has been awake after surgery, transplantation of good oxygen function of lung function, stable vital signs.
陈静瑜说，新冠肺炎病例接受肺移植手术最主要有三个医学前提条件：一是病人经呼吸机+ ECMO维持，双肺呼吸衰竭不可逆；二是核酸检测连续多次呈阴性；三是其他脏器功能基本正常，全身状况能够承受肺移植手术。
Chen said there were three main medical preconditions for a lung transplant operation: one was irreversible respiratory failure sustained by a ventilator + ECMO; the other was multiple negative nucleic acid tests; and the other organ function was basically normal, allowing the patient to withstand a lung transplant.
“这类手术风险很大，移植医护人员要在负压手术室间、全程穿着隔离防护服开展手术，对心理和体力考验极大。
"The risks are so great that transplant staff have to operate in vacuum operating rooms and wear protective clothing all the way through," he said.
”陈静瑜说，“为了病人移植手术成功、同时力争医护人员零感染，在江苏省市领导支持下，医疗团队术前进行了周密的部署准备工作，下一步团队将密切维护好病人，重点探索此类患者的围术期管理，做好移植后抗排异、抗感染后续治疗，总结经验为更多晚期的新冠肺炎危重症病例救治打开希望之门。
"In order for patients to have successful transplant operations and strive for zero infections among medical staff, the medical team, with the support of Jiangsu city leaders, conducted thorough pre-operation preparations, focusing on perioperative management of such patients.
”本期编辑 周玉华推荐阅读。
Zhou Yuhua, editor of this issue, recommends reading.
